<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-30T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="669" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/281: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-30T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    August 30, 4.36 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Chinese Government inquires of the Diplomatic Corps whether the embargo
                            on arms and ammunition includes raw material for the manufacture of the
                            same. I have the honor to request your instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>